==English==
===Alternative spellings===
*[[mantlet]]

===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[#Old French|mantelet]]'', diminutive of ''[[mantel]]'' ‘mantle’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈmæntlɪt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A short sleeveless [[cloak]] or [[cape]].
# {{military}} A portable [[screen]] or other covering, especially as used to protect the approach of soldiers engaged in a siege.
#:*'''1819''': They bring forward '''mantelets''' and pavisses, and the archers muster on the skirts of the wood like a dark cloud before a hailstorm. — Walter Scott, ''Ivanhoe''

